    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-24T10:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-24T10:40:00-05:00" n="793"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00 Revolutions/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-24T11:00:00-04:40"
                            >February 24, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. The Vice President has presented his resignation and the Dominican Government
                    promises legislative annullment of all amendments to the electoral law made
                    since 1924. With this information Cabot<note n="4" xml:id="d793fn4">John Moors
                        Cabot, Third Secretary of Legation.</note> has gone to endeavor to prevent
                    bloodshed between the revolutionists and the troops sent out to stop them. The
                    retirement of Alfonseca should restore to the Government the firm allegiance of
                    the Government’s leaders throughout the country. There is no reliable news from
                    Santiago which is almost certainly in the possession of the revolutionists.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
